step_data.thought:
I'm now on the product page for 'VARIETY SET OF 5 NK Hydrating Lip Gel - Vitamin E' and I can see that I've successfully navigated to the Reviews tab as it shows 'Reviews (12)' and the customer reviews are displayed. This product has an 87% rating with 12 reviews, which is quite high.

Looking through the reviews, I can see:
1. Most reviews give this product 5 stars (100% rating)
2. There is one very negative review with 1 star (20% rating) mentioning an allergic reaction
3. Positive aspects mentioned:
   - Moisturizing and hydrating
   - Long-lasting
   - Nice scents/flavors
   - Good value for price
   - Makes lips look glossy and feel soft
4. Negative aspects mentioned:
   - One user had an allergic reaction with swelling
   - Different consistency than average gloss (though some see this as a positive)

I've now examined two of the highest-rated lip products:
1. DOLL FACE Lip Gloss (88% rating)
2. VARIETY SET OF 5 NK Hydrating Lip Gel (87% rating)

I've successfully completed the task of finding the best-rated lip products and reading their customer reviews. I should now send a message to the user summarizing my findings.
step_data.action:
stop('Based on my search, I found two top-rated lip products with extensive customer reviews:

1. DOLL FACE Lip Gloss | Glitterazzi Liquid Lip Bling (88% rating, 12 reviews)
   - Pros: Beautiful shimmer, non-sticky, good color, moisturizing
   - Cons: Not long-lasting, can get tacky with multiple coats

2. VARIETY SET OF 5 NK Hydrating Lip Gel - Vitamin E (87% rating, 12 reviews)
   - Pros: Very moisturizing, long-lasting, nice scents, good value
   - Cons: One user reported an allergic reaction, different consistency than typical gloss

Both products are highly rated, with the NK Hydrating Lip Gel having more consistently positive reviews but one concerning allergic reaction report.')
